        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. Diagnosis of untreated unruptured intracranial aneurysm (by CTA, MRA or DSA);

          2. Patient with premorbid mRS of 3 or less;

          3. Patient older than 14years;

          4. Patient consenting to participate to the study;

          5. Patients with a definite history of ischemic heart disease or ischemic stroke who
             accept antithrombotic or anticoagulant therapy for secondary pevention

        Exclusion Criteria:

        Subarachnoid hemorrhage with unknown causes;

        - Page 4 of 4 [DRAFT] - 2. Patient with other cerebral arteriovenous malformations or
        cerebral arteriovenous fistulas; 3. Patient with malignant tumor; 4. Target aneurysm is
        fusiform, traumatic, mycotic, or dissecting related; 5. Inability to obtain informed
        consent; 6. Patients with a life expectancy less than 1 year; 7. Participating in the other
        clinical studies of intracranial aneurysm; 8. Refusal of follow-up
